    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverioDAI2"/>, p. 117, n. <citedRange>117</citedRange>, fig. 73</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.229</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>027300</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#beschi1970"/>, pp. <citedRange>181</citedRange>, and fig. 36, <citedRange>185-186, 204</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#laronde1987"/>, pp. <citedRange>52-58</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>38.1892</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.8</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/>, p. <citedRange>103</citedRange> with footnote 94</bibl> (prosopography).</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-66074"><name nymRef="#Φίλων">Φίλων</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65032"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Μνάσαρχος">Μνασάρχω</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Philon fils de Mnasarkhos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Philon son of Mnasarchos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Philon figlio di Mnasarchos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>فيلون بن مناسارخوس</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p> Philon was a member of a the prominent family (for which see <bibl><ptr target="#laronde1987"/>, pp. <citedRange>52-58</citedRange></bibl>), whose monumental tomb is well known.</p>
	      <p>Beschi was able to show that the mourning half-figure 39 of his catalogue stood on this base.</p>
	<p>The photograph of the view is part of a larger photograph showing the discovey of the bases, displayed in front of tomb N171, with help of Italian soldiers 
	in 1915-1916. This photograph is kept in the archive of the Society for Libyan Studies. All bases are now kept inside the tomb in a side room with restricted access.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
